short-reads/2026/05/26/facts-about-marijuana/</guid></item><item><title>美国人的工资跟得上通货膨胀吗？这取决于</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/05/21/have-americans-wages-kept-up-with-inflation-that-depends/</link><description>确定工人的工资是否跟上通货膨胀取决于许多因素。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 22 May 2026 02:05:54 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/05/21/have-americans-wages-kept-up-with-inflation-that-depends/</guid></item><item><title>关于美国人和心理健康的主要发现</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/05/20/key-findings-about-americans-and-mental-health/</link><description>在全国纪念心理健康意识月之际，以下是美国人如何描述他们的心理健康以及他们愿意与谁谈论心理健康。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 21 May 2026 02:04:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/05/20/key-findings-about-americans-and-mental-health/</guid></item><item><title>关于非洲人口增长的 5 个事实</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/05/19/5-facts-about-africas-population-growth/</link><description>尽管预计本世纪剩余时间全球人口增长将放缓，但非洲因其相对年轻且不断增长的人口而脱颖而出。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 14:31:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/05/19/5-facts-about-africas-population-growth/</guid></item><item><title>特朗普在拉丁裔选民中的支持率跌至第二任期低点，但许多人仍然支持</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/05/15/trumps-approval-rating-hits-second-term-low-among-his-latino-voters-though-many-still-approve/</link><description>大约三分之二的拉丁裔特朗普选民（66%）认可他的工作表现。自他第二任期开始以来，这一数字下降了 27 个百分点。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 16 May 2026 01:51:48 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/05/15/trumps-approval-rating-hits-second-term-low-among-his-latino-voters-though-many-still-approve/</guid></item><item><title>大多数美国人说这个国家最好的岁月已经过去</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/05/15/a-majority-of-americans-say-the-countrys-best-years-are-behind-us/</link><description>当被问及 50 年后美国的情况时，美国人的悲观情绪 (44%) 远高于乐观情绪 (28%)。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 16 May 2026 01:36:48 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/05/15/a-majority-of-americans-say-the-countrys-best-years-are-behind-us/</guid></item><item><title>美国人认为怎样才能成为好新闻消费者</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/05/14/what-americans-think-it-takes-to-be-a-good-news-consumer/</link><description>美国人最常联想到的好消息消费者之一就是怀疑感或洞察力。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 15 May 2026 01:59:08 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/05/14/what-americans-think-it-takes-to-be-a-good-news-consumer/</guid></item></channel></rss>